								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"editTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T22:32:31.624195+01:00"
								}
							},
							"uid" : {
								"__type" : "uid",
								"uidString" : "MXU1sovxRie49dbz7oOMaw=="
							},
							"paragraphStyle" : {
								"__type" : "textStyle"
							},
							"string" : "For example, suppose we want to preview proposed changes from the LLM. In that case, we can specify that we expect code transformations. To add a new response schema, we use {{gtMethod:GtLChat>>#addResponseFormatForMagrite:named:}}, which takes the schema from a Magritte class. In our case, the class is {{gtClass:GtLCodeTransformations}}, which, besides describing the structure of different kinds of transformations, also knows how to turn those transformations into dedicated changes that can be applied directly in the image:"
						}
					]
				},
